                22</ref>)<marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></enactingFormula><commencementNote>[2 January 1976]</commencementNote><sourceNote>(Format changes—<ref href="hk/2017/er1">E.R. 1 of 2017</ref>)</sourceNote><section id="ID_1438403394492_004" name="s1" reason="inEffect" role="regulation" startPeriod="2017-02-15" status="operational" temporalId="s1"><num value="1">1.</num><heading>Citation</heading><content>These regulations may be cited as the Antiquities (Excavation and Search) Regulations.</content></section><section id="ID_1438403394508_002" name="s2" reason="inEffect" role="regulation" startPeriod="2017-02-15" status="operational" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Application for licence</heading><subsection id="ID_1438413121884_011" name="1" temporalId="s2_1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content>Subject to paragraph (2), a person who desires to obtain a licence shall apply to the Authority in triplicate in Form I in the <ref>Schedule</ref> at least 2 months before the date upon which the excavation and search is intended to commence.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1438413121884_019" name="2" temporalId="s2_2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content>Notwithstanding paragraph (1), the Authority may consider an application not made within the time prescribed.</content></subsection></section><section id="ID_1438403394508_004" name="s3" reason="inEffect" role="regulation" startPeriod="2017-02-15" status="operational" temporalId="s3"><num value="3">3.</num><heading>Plans and photographs</heading><content>An application to obtain a licence shall be accompanied by a plan in triplicate on a scale not smaller than 1:1200 showing the location, boundaries and general features of the area in respect of which the licence is sought and the particular site, if any, of the proposed excavation, together with a photograph or photographs each not smaller than 25 centimetres by 20 centimetres sufficient to identify and describe the area under application, to the satisfaction of the Authority.</content></section><section id="ID_1438403394523_002" name="s4" reason="inEffect" role="regulation" startPeriod="2017-02-15" status="operational" temporalId="s4"><num value="4">4.</num><heading>Application to renew licence</heading><subsection id="ID_1438413121931_011" name="1" temporalId="s4_1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content>Subject to paragraph (2), an application to renew a licence shall be made at least 1 month before the date upon which the licence is due to expire and shall be made in such manner and shall contain such information as the Authority considers appropriate.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1438413121931_019" name="2" temporalId="s4_2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content>Notwithstanding paragraph (1) the Authority may consider an application not made within the time prescribed.</content></subsection></section><section id="ID_1438403394539_001" name="s5" reason="inEffect" role="regulation" startPeriod="2017-02-15" status="operational" temporalId="s5"><num value="5">5.</num><heading>Licence</heading><content>A licence shall be in Form II in the <ref>Schedule</ref>.</content></section><section id="ID_1438403394539_003" name="s6" reason="inEffect" role="regulation" startPeriod="2017-02-15" status="operational" temporalId="s6"><num value="6">6.</num><heading>Fees</heading><content>There shall be payable to the Authority upon the grant or renewal of a licence a fee of $2,520.</content><sourceNote>(<ref href="/hk/1995/ln190">L.N. 190 of 1995</ref>; <ref href="hk/2016/ln9">L.N. 9 of 2016</ref>)</sourceNote></section><schedule id="ID_1438403394555_001" name="sch0" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2017-02-15" status="operational" temporalId="sch0"><num value="0">Schedule</num><crossHeading>Form
